You can add a chart to any report thatâ€™s grouped by rows (summary report) or rows and columns (matrix report). The chart properties specify the data that appears in the chart, its labels and colors, and any conditional highlighting.

Chart Data Settings

FIELD  DESCRIPTION
Chart Type  Select the type of chart to use when representing the data in your report.
X-Axis and Y-Axis  Choose what values to display on the axes of your chart.
Combination Chart  Select this option to plot additional values on this chart.
Groupings  Choose how to group information on your chart.
Values  Choose what to display as values for your pie, donut, or funnel charts.
Conditional Highlighting

FIELD  DESCRIPTION
Summary  Choose a summary field whose number ranges you want represented by colors.
Low Color  Select a color to represent data that falls below the Low Breakpoint value.
Low Breakpoint  The number that acts as the threshold between the Low Color and the Mid Color.
Mid Color  Select a color to represent data that falls between the Low Breakpoint and High Breakpoint values.
High Breakpoint  The number that acts as the threshold between the Mid Color and the High Color.
High Color  Select a color to represent data that falls above the High Breakpoint value.
